We've all seen the movies, played the games, and read the books that foretold us about a society populated by machines and governed by AI and now, fleets of fully autonomous, self-driving vehicles have hit the streets in cities around the world. Companies like Google, Amazon, and Tesla, are leading the charge to this brave new world, driven by the promises of a technocratic utopia, but is that a road humanity wants go down?
